ight small">Janna Levin</span></a></div><p class="h6 o6 mv1 pv025"><em>August 1, 2024</em></p></div><div class="post__title__meta flex flex-wrap flex-items-start"><div class="post__title__excerpt wysiwyg p italic mb1 mt025 pr2 o4 theme__text">Cryptography is the thread that connects Julius Caesar, World War II and quantum computing, and it now lies under nearly every part of modern life. In this week’s episode, computer scientist Boaz Barak and co-host Janna Levin discuss the past and future of secrecy.</div><div class="post__title__actions h5 mt025 flex-auto flex flex-items-center"><div class="comments-button mr05 flex flex-items-center theme__accent"><a href="#comments" class="flex flex-items-center pangram"><svg viewBox="0 0 50 50" enable-background="new 0 0 50 50"><title>Comment</title><path fill="currentColor" d="M9.4 4.2h31.2c8.6 0 9.4 7 9.4 15.6s-.7 15.6-9.4 15.6h-2.2l-.9 9.4-18.8-9.4H9.4c-8.6 0-9.4-7-9.4-15.6S.7 4.2 9.4 4.2z"></path></svg><div><span class="comments-button__count ml075 small mbold disqus-comment-count" data-disqus-identifier="139467 https://www.quantamagazine.org/?p=139467"></span></div></a></div><span class="o-divider mh075 relative"></span><div class="relative"><button class="bookmark-button mh05 flex flex-items-center theme__accent-hover" aria-expanded="false"><svg class="icon" viewBox="0 0 50 50" enable-background="new 0 0 50 50"><title>Save Article</title><path fill="currentColor" d="M2.1 0h45.8v50L25.5 37.5 2.1 50V0z"></path></svg></button><div class="q-tooltip hidden force-mobile-placement" style="width:130px;top:55px;margin-left:-65px"><div class="q-tooltip-content"><div class="q-tooltip-arrow"></div><div class="q-tooltip-inner" role="tooltip"><div class="h6t relative z1 uppercase kern--w mx025"><span class="small no-wrap">Read Later</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></section></div><figure class="lh-0 w-100P m-0_auto d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center flex-direction-column max-w